headline.print_headline: Mexico Rescues 39 Kidnapped Central American Immigrants
headline.main: Mexico Rescues 39 Kidnapped Central American Immigrants

lead_paragraph: Local police and federal soldiers rescued 39 Central American immigrants on Monday at a residence in the northern border state of Tamaulipas, state security authorities said in a statement on Tuesday.
